                       FidoNews Generator is Offline


     The  system  that  creates  FidoNews  every  week  has suffered a
     hardware attack.  We are engaged in major surgery to  revive  it,
     but the prognosis is not good.

     In  other words,  my system died and I have been unable to get it
     up and running reliably.  Plans made long ago call for  my  being
     away  for  the next two weeks,  and I have no time left to get it
     fixed before I leave.  This unfortunate timing of events means:

      1) It will be AT LEAST three weeks  before I can publish another
         issue of FidoNews.

      2) The  files  mentioned  in  last  week's  FidoNews  as   being
         requestable  from  107/6  or  downloadable  from our BBS will
         probably not be available for at least another two weeks.

      3) Nodes in Region 13 may  experience  difficulties  in  getting
         their  node  list updates in,  or in receiving new node lists
         over the next two or three weeks.

     I will endeavor to get the problems fixed  as  soon  as  possible
     upon my return.  Until then, you have my apologies in advance for
     whatever inconveniences may occur.


     -----------------------------------------------------------------

     Substitute Editor's note:  Rather than publish absolutely nothing
     for a 3-week period,  Thom has arranged for one of his underlings
     to pinch-hit with this abbreviated edition.

     However,  we don't know yet what we'll do next week.  Maybe it'll
     be "The Best of FIDONEWS."

