                     IFNA Status Report for October 1987


     This is the first of what should be a  monthly status report from
     me to  the membership  of  IFNA.   It is my intention  to publish
     these reports here in FidoNews the  first week of each month from
     now until  the end of  my term in August.   My apologies for this
     report being a week late - this was due to technical difficulties
     experienced with both my machine and the one supporting FidoNews.

     I have requested that  all of the Committee  Chairmen  provide me
     with Status Reports outlining their Progress  for the past month,
     current Problems, and Prognosis for the coming month.   My status
     report to you, which will take the  same general format,  will be
     based on  their  reporting and on  additional  material  from the
     various officers of the Association.


     PROGRESS DURING THIS PERIOD

     General
       Well, we're underway!   We may not have a full head of steam up
       yet, but at least we seem to be moving a bit  -  and much of it
       is in the same general direction for a change!

     Administration and Finance
       We still do not have an official Chairperson for this committee
       so Ken Kaplan continues  as Acting Chairman.   He and Treasurer
       Leonard Mednick  have been in contact and intend to meet in St.
       Louis in order to perform a turnover of responsibilities.

     Board of Directors
       The BoD has formed its own echo and has  discussed a variety of
       concerns.   To date, however,  progress on any one  these items
       has  been stymied by a  lack of structure.   One question  that
       appears to  have been resolved is the question of whether a new
       node in South Africa  should be allowed  to join FidoNet.   The
       consensus  appears to be that,  as FidoNet is  dedicated to the
       free and open exchange of information,  it may prove beneficial
       (even  in some small way)  to admit any node  that  ascribes to
       those precepts.

     FidoNews 4-39                Page 5                   12 Oct 1987



     By-laws and Rules
       The primary  activity of  this commmittee  this month  has just
       been the manning of the committee.

     Executive Committee
       This committee has formed its own Echo and has begun discussion
       on a variety of topics.   No specific decisions  have been made
       to this point, however.

     International Affairs
       This committee  has not "met" as of yet,  although  Henk Wevers
       has provided some assistance to Switzerland which has scheduled
       its first National Sysop Meeting for the first weekend in
       October.

     Membership Services
       Phil Ardussi sent in a very nice report  which I've summarized.
       Committee   organization  included  the  formation   of several
       sub-committees: FidoCon Site Selection (Jim Cannell),  Echolist
       (Gene Coppola), Help Node (David Dodell), New Sysop Help (David
       Bonine),  and  Membership  List  (Norm Henke).    Several other
       projects are under way including requests for proposals for the
       site of the next FidoNet Conference.

     Nominations and Elections
       Dave Dodell informs me  that he has  formed his commmittee  but
       they have tabled any action at this time  as it is too early to
       gear up for the next elections.

     Publications
       No detailed report has been received from this committee.

     Technical Standards
       Ryugen Fisher says that the  following sub-committees have been
       formed (or established liaison) and been manned: New Protocols,
       Documentation, Beta Testing, 9600 Modems, FOSSIL.


